---
description: >
  Jobpal is a career operating system for job seekers. It keeps one trusted
  career profile, tailors resumes and cover letters to a role, discovers relevant
  live jobs, tracks applications from Gmail, prepares users for interviews, and
  helps fill job application forms through a Chromium extension.
---

***definitions***

- :App: is the Jobpal career operating system for job seekers.

- :User: is a job seeker using :App: to manage applications and profile.

- :FallbackMode: is the deterministic local behavior :App: uses when optional
  service credentials are unavailable.
  - Used for profile extraction, resume generation, and job discovery.
  - Produces honest demo data instead of failures.

- :AuthSession: is the authenticated session for a :User: in :App:.
  - Created at sign-in via Supabase Auth (when configured) or local demo auth.
  - Tracks the :User: identity across screens and API calls.

- :CareerProfile: is the master profile for a :User:, the source of truth for
  all generated documents and recommendations.
  - Contains contact details, professional summary, skills, work experience,
    education, and projects.
  - Sections can be edited individually.
  - Required fields must be present before resume generation.
  - Optional sections can remain empty.

- :ResumeSourceFile: is an uploaded resume file from :User: in PDF or DOCX
  format.
  - Extracted into text before conversion to :CareerProfile:.
  - Rejected if empty or unsupported format.

- :ProfileExtraction: is the conversion of extracted resume text into a
  structured :CareerProfile:.
  - Uses Azure AI Foundry when configured; deterministic mock when not.
  - Produces a profile ready for user review and editing.

- :JobDescription: is the text of a job posting provided by :User: as either
  pasted text or a URL.
  - Extracted from supported public job pages when provided as URL.
  - Falls back to pasted text if URL extraction fails.
  - Rejected if empty or too vague.

- :ResumeTemplate: is an ATS-friendly resume layout option :User: can choose.
  - Determines visual presentation of a :TailoredResume:.
  - Multiple templates available; :User: can switch and preview instantly.

- :TailoredResume: is a resume generated from :CareerProfile: and
  :JobDescription: for a specific role.
  - Preserves truthful employers, dates, education, and achievements.
  - Rewords existing experience with role-specific language.
  - Never invents missing facts.
  - Uses chosen :ResumeTemplate: for formatting.

- :CoverLetter: is a cover letter generated from :CareerProfile: and
  :JobDescription: for a specific role.
  - Avoids copying :TailoredResume: bullets verbatim.
  - Uses role-specific motivation and fit.
  - Never introduces unverified claims.

- :SavedResume: is a :TailoredResume: and :CoverLetter: pair saved by :User:
  for later reference.
  - Stores company name, role title, template choice, and creation timestamp.
  - Can be reopened and regenerated.
  - Identified by ID; missing resumes return not-found states.

- :JobSource: is a public job board or ATS offering direct job listings.
  - Supported sources include Greenhouse, Lever, Ashby, Workable,
    SmartRecruiters.

- :JobPosting: is a job listing from a :JobSource:.
  - Normalized into a common shape across all sources.
  - Never fabricated; always from live provider data.

- :JobAlertFilter: is the configuration :User: creates to discover jobs.
  - Supports keywords, location, country, arrangement, type, salary, level.
  - Keywords can be inferred from :CareerProfile: if left empty.
  - Invalid salary and location filters are rejected.

- :JobMatchScore: is the confidence score for how well a :JobPosting: matches
  :CareerProfile:.
  - Calculated from profile data; lower confidence when data is missing.
  - Used to rank jobs in alerts.

- :ApplicationTracker: is the record of job applications for :User:, sourced
  both manually and from Gmail.
  - Manually entered applications are created and edited by :User:.
  - Gmail-derived applications are auto-extracted from hiring emails.

- :TrackedApplication: is a single application entry tracking a job search.
  - Contains company name, role title, :ApplicationStatus:, and timestamps.
  - Can be manually created and edited by :User:.
  - Can be auto-updated from :EmailMessage: analysis.

- :ApplicationStatus: is one of five statuses for a :TrackedApplication:.
  - Applied, In Review, Interview, Decision, Archived.

- :EmailMessage: is a message from Gmail linked to a :TrackedApplication:.
  - Extracted read-only via Gmail OAuth.
  - Classified to identify hiring company, ATS vendor, and intent.
  - Kept idempotent by message ID to prevent duplicates.

- :TrackerSync: is the process of refreshing :ApplicationTracker: with new
  :EmailMessage: entries from Gmail.
  - Only syncs after Gmail connection.
  - Updates :TrackedApplication: status when emails indicate progress.

- :InterviewPrep: is preparation material generated for a :TrackedApplication:.
  - Includes company context, role themes, likely questions, talking points.
  - Lower-confidence note when company data is missing.
  - Does not change application status.

- :BillingPlan: is a subscription tier offering a monthly quota of tailored
  documents.
  - Free and paid plans defined.
  - Quota consumed only after successful generation.

- :UsageQuota: is the monthly document-generation quota for a :User: under a
  :BillingPlan:.
  - Enforced before generation; not consumed on validation or provider failures.
  - Displayed after successful generation.

- :MagicFillExtension: is the Chromium extension that auto-fills job
  application forms.
  - Manifest V3 package; separate from web app.
  - Detects form fields and maps to :CareerProfile: values.

- :ExtensionSession: is the authenticated session for :MagicFillExtension:.
  - Exchanged from web auth; refreshable via refresh credentials.
  - Revokable; blocks profile and document access after revocation.

- :DetectedField: is a form field on a job application detected by
  :MagicFillExtension:.
  - Mapped to :CareerProfile: values.
  - High-confidence fields are auto-fillable.
  - Ambiguous fields are kept for user review.

- :FieldMemory: is stored field mapping history for :DetectedField: on a
  specific website.
  - Used to improve :DetectedField: detection on repeated visits.

- :ProductScreenMap: is the inventory of :App: screens and their purposes.
  - Documents user journeys and entry points.

- :ProductApiMap: is the inventory of :App: API routes and their expected
  purposes.
  - Documents all backend surfaces.

***implementation reqs***

- :Implementation: should be in TypeScript with strict mode enabled.

- :Implementation: should use Next.js App Router (not Pages router) for all
  screens and API routes.

- :Implementation: should use React for client-side component rendering and
  interactivity.

- :Implementation: should use Zod for runtime validation of profile, resume,
  job, cover letter, and tracker data.

- :Implementation: should use Supabase Postgres as the primary persistent
  storage when Supabase credentials are configured.

- :Implementation: should fall back to local JSON file storage (in-memory or
  local filesystem) when Supabase credentials are unavailable.

- :Implementation: should use Supabase Auth for sign-in and session management
  when configured, and local ephemeral sessions for demo mode.

- :Implementation: should use Azure AI Foundry for LLM tasks (profile
  extraction, resume/cover letter generation, interview prep) when credentials
  are available.

- :Implementation: should use deterministic mock generation (hardcoded sample
  data) for LLM tasks when Azure credentials are unavailable.

- :Implementation: should integrate directly with Greenhouse, Lever, Ashby,
  Workable, and SmartRecruiters public job listing APIs for job discovery.

- :Implementation: should use Gmail read-only OAuth for application tracking
  and email sync.

- :Implementation: should use Dodo Payments for checkout and customer portal
  when API key is configured, and local billing simulation-only mode when
  unavailable.

- :Implementation: should use Cloudflare R2 for archival storage of original
  uploaded resume files when credentials are present; skip upload to R2 when
  unavailable without breaking the resume upload flow.

- :Implementation: should organize source code as follows:
  - `src/app/` contains Next.js App Router pages, layouts, and API routes.
  - `src/components/` contains reusable UI, layout, auth, and resume-editing
    components.
  - `src/lib/schema/` contains Zod schemas for all domain models.
  - `src/lib/db/` contains store abstraction interface and concrete
    implementations (Supabase and local JSON).
  - `src/lib/llm/` contains Azure AI Foundry client and mock LLM client.
  - `src/lib/parsing/` contains text extraction from uploaded resumes and job
    URLs.
  - `src/lib/templates/` contains ATS-friendly resume layout templates.
  - `src/lib/jobs/` contains job discovery, normalization, deduplication,
    filtering, and scoring logic.
  - `src/lib/tracker/` contains Gmail connection, email classification,
    message linking, and sync logic.
  - `src/lib/billing/` contains plan definitions, quota enforcement, checkout,
    customer portal, and webhook handling.
  - `src/lib/extension/` contains extension session auth, field detection,
    field memory, and magic-fill logic.
  - `extension/` is a separate Chromium Manifest V3 package, built with Vite,
    independent of the web app.

- :Implementation: should run the web app on port 3002.

- :Implementation: should never expose service-role keys, OAuth secrets,
  provider tokens, or billing secrets to client-side code.

- :Implementation: should store all OAuth tokens server-side; never transmit
  them to the browser.

***functional specs***

- Resolve :AuthSession: and enforce sign-in on private screens.
  - Before rendering any screen behind authentication, resolve the signed-in
    :User: from :AuthSession:.
  - If no :AuthSession: exists, redirect unauthenticated browser requests to
    /login.
  - This applies to all screens except /login itself.
  - API routes do not redirect; see the next auth specs for API error handling.

- Create and manage local demo :AuthSession: when Supabase Auth is not
  configured.
  - When :App: starts without Supabase Auth credentials, create an ephemeral
    :AuthSession: for a demo :User: with a randomized session ID.
  - The demo :User: can use all :App: functionality identically to a real
    :User:.
  - All demo data is stored in memory or local storage and is lost when the
    session ends.
  - The UI should visibly label all screens as demo mode.

- Return JSON authorization errors from all API routes.
  - Every API route returns structured JSON error responses instead of HTML
    redirects.
  - On missing or invalid :AuthSession:, return HTTP 401 Unauthorized with a
    JSON body containing an error code and message.
  - On valid :AuthSession: but insufficient permissions to access another
    :User:'s data, return HTTP 403 Forbidden with a JSON body containing an
    error code and message.

- Scope all user data reads and writes to the authenticated :User:.
  - Every API route that accesses, modifies, or returns profile, resumes,
    tracker, billing, or extension data validates that the requested :User: ID
    matches the authenticated :AuthSession:.
  - If the IDs do not match, return HTTP 403 Forbidden.
  - This applies to all CRUD operations (create, read, update, delete) on
    user-scoped resources.

- Display onboarding entry screen where :User: chooses upload or manual
  profile entry.
  - On the /onboarding screen, present two options: "Upload Resume" (goes to
    /intake) and "Build Manually" (goes to /builder).
  - Either choice leads to :CareerProfile: creation.

- Accept resume file upload in PDF or DOCX format.
  - On /intake, accept file uploads; reject empty files, unsupported formats,
    and files >10MB with clear error messages before parsing.

- Extract text from uploaded :ResumeSourceFile:.
  - Parse PDF and DOCX files to extract plain text.
  - Handle parse errors with a user-facing message.
  - Do not proceed if text extraction fails.

- Convert extracted resume text to structured :CareerProfile: using LLM or
  mock.
  - Send extracted text to Azure AI Foundry to identify contact details,
    summary, skills, experience, education, projects.
  - Use deterministic mock data when Azure credentials are unavailable.
  - Present results as editable defaults on /builder.

- Let :User: enter career story as free-form text and convert to
  :CareerProfile:.
  - On /builder (manual path), accept multi-line text entry for career
    narrative.
  - Send to Azure (or use mock) to extract structure.
  - Present results as editable fields.

- Show :CareerProfile: fields for review and editing on /builder.
  - Display all profile sections (contact, summary, skills, experience,
    education, projects) with extracted/mock values pre-filled and directly
    editable.
  - Let :User: add, remove, or modify entries in each section.

- Validate :CareerProfile: and show errors for required fields.
  - Require contact details (name, email), summary, skills, and work
    experience before :User: can proceed to generate resumes.
  - Show clear errors for missing required fields.

- Allow optional profile sections to remain empty.
  - Projects and education are optional.
  - Do not block generation if empty.
  - Let :User: skip or fill them later.

- Save :CareerProfile: edits and persist before resume generation.
  - When :User: clicks save or proceeds to generation, persist all edited
    profile fields to the database (or local storage in demo mode).
  - Persist before any generation step uses the profile.

- Let :User: input :JobDescription: via paste or URL.
  - On /customize, accept either pasted text or a URL to a public job posting.
  - Validate that at least one is provided.

- Extract :JobDescription: text from supported public job pages.
  - When :User: provides a URL, attempt to scrape and extract the job
    description text.
  - Supported sources: Greenhouse, Lever, Ashby, Workable, SmartRecruiters.
  - If extraction fails, notify :User: and allow fallback to pasted text.

- Fall back to pasted :JobDescription: when URL extraction fails or source
  unsupported.
  - If URL scraping fails or the domain is unsupported, use the pasted job
    description text if provided.
  - If neither extraction nor paste succeeded, return an error.

- Reject empty or vague :JobDescription: with clear guidance.
  - Validate that :JobDescription: is non-empty and contains recognizable
    job-related keywords (title, responsibilities, requirements).
  - Reject with user-facing message if too vague.

- Generate :TailoredResume: from :CareerProfile: and :JobDescription:.
  - Use Azure AI Foundry to create a resume tailored to the job.
  - Preserve truthful employers, dates, education, projects, achievements.
  - Reword existing experience with role-specific language.
  - Never invent missing facts.
  - Use :FallbackMode: mock if Azure unavailable.

- Let :User: choose :ResumeTemplate: for :TailoredResume: formatting and
  preview instantly.
  - Display available ATS-friendly templates.
  - When :User: selects a template, update the live preview immediately.

- Generate :CoverLetter: using :CareerProfile: and :JobDescription:.
  - Create a cover letter for the same role.
  - Avoid copying :TailoredResume: bullets verbatim.
  - Use role-specific motivation and fit.
  - Use Azure or :FallbackMode: mock as needed.

- Support flexible document generation (resume-only, cover-letter-only, or
  both).
  - Allow :User: to choose which documents to generate in a single call.
  - Return only the selected documents.
  - Both are optional but at least one must be selected.

- Save :SavedResume: with company, role, template choice, and creation
  timestamp.
  - After generation, let :User: save the resume pair.
  - Store company name, role title, template name, and creation time.
  - Identify :SavedResume: by unique ID.

- Allow :User: to reopen and regenerate saved :SavedResume: entries.
  - From /resumes screen, :User: can view, edit metadata (company, role),
    and regenerate a saved resume.
  - Can regenerate with the same or different :JobDescription:.

- Return not-found state for missing or deleted :SavedResume:.
  - If :User: requests a :SavedResume: by ID that does not exist, return a
    404 with clear message.

- Provide PDF export for :TailoredResume: and :CoverLetter:.
  - Generate downloadable PDF versions of both documents.
  - Preserve formatting and ATS-friendliness.

- Enforce monthly tailored-document quota before generation.
  - Before generating any resume or cover letter, check :UsageQuota: against
    :BillingPlan:.
  - If quota exhausted, show user error with upgrade link.
  - Do not generate.

- Consume quota only after successful generation.
  - Quota is consumed only after documents are successfully generated.
  - Validation errors, scraping failures, or provider failures do not consume
    quota.

- Integrate Dodo checkout and customer portal when configured.
  - When Dodo API key is present, wire /api/billing/checkout to Dodo checkout
    flow.
  - Wire /api/billing/portal to customer portal.
  - Use local simulation-only mode when Dodo unavailable.

- Configure :JobAlertFilter: with keywords, location, level, type.
  - Let :User: set keywords (inferred from :CareerProfile: if empty),
    location, country, arrangement, salary range, job level.
  - Validate location and salary before calling providers.

- Query Greenhouse, Lever, Ashby, Workable, SmartRecruiters for jobs.
  - Call all configured :JobSource: endpoints in parallel.
  - Normalize results to common :JobPosting: shape.
  - Deduplicate by title + company across sources.

- Score and rank :JobPosting: against :CareerProfile: and show results.
  - Score each job using profile data.
  - Lower confidence when profile data is missing.
  - Display in ranked order.
  - Show partial results if one provider fails.
  - Show empty state if no jobs found.

- Let :User: manually create and edit :TrackedApplication: entries.
  - On /tracker, accept company, role, and :ApplicationStatus: as required fields.
  - Allow :User: to create new entries or edit existing ones.
  - Manual edits take priority over automated guesses from emails.

- Connect Gmail with read-only OAuth and sync :EmailMessage: entries.
  - Show disabled state when Google OAuth is not configured.
  - On connection, sync new messages from Gmail and classify each.
  - Link messages to :TrackedApplication: where possible using company/hiring
    keywords.
  - Keep processing idempotent by message ID; do not create duplicates.

- Update :ApplicationStatus: when :EmailMessage: indicate progress.
  - Parse emails for signals (interview offer, rejection, review confirmation).
  - Update status accordingly (applied → interview, applied → rejected, etc.).

- Generate :InterviewPrep: from tracked application.
  - Include company context, role themes, likely questions, talking points.
  - Lower-confidence note when company data is missing.
  - Do not change :ApplicationStatus: when generating.

- Define :MagicFillExtension: as separate Manifest V3 package.
  - Extension authenticates via :ExtensionSession: from web app.
  - Detects form fields on job application pages.
  - Maps fields to :CareerProfile: values and suggests fills.
  - High-confidence fields are auto-fillable; ambiguous ones kept for review.

- Exchange web auth for :ExtensionSession: and support refresh + revoke.
  - /api/extension/auth/exchange trades web session for extension session.
  - :ExtensionSession: is refreshable when credentials exist.
  - Revoke endpoint blocks profile and document access after revocation.

***test reqs***

- :UnitTests: should use Jest framework for the web app.

- :UnitTests: should be located in `src/**/*.test.ts` and `src/**/*.test.tsx`
  files alongside implementation.

- :ConformanceTests: should use Jest + Supertest for HTTP API testing.

- :ConformanceTests: should be located in `conformance_tests/` directory
  organized by feature.

- :ConformanceTests: should test all API routes against a running local Next.js
  server.

- :ConformanceTests: should verify that :CareerProfile:, :TailoredResume:,
  :CoverLetter:, :SavedResume:, :JobPosting:, :TrackedApplication:, and
  :BillingPlan: endpoints conform to the functional spec behavior.

- :ConformanceTests: should use mocked external services (Azure, Gmail,
  Greenhouse, etc.) or sandbox credentials when testing locally.
